1
00:00:56,073 --> 00:00:58,868
FILING FOR LOVE

2
00:01:06,625 --> 00:01:08,919
SENDER: NONAME
TITLE: REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

3
00:01:09,003 --> 00:01:10,921
SHE IS INVOLVED IN AN INAPPROPRIATE
WORKPLACE RELATIONSHIP

4
00:01:25,811 --> 00:01:27,563
HIDE SENDER ID
TITLE: REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

5
00:01:27,646 --> 00:01:28,814
SHE IS INVOLVED IN
AN INAPPROPRIATE...

6
00:01:31,817 --> 00:01:32,943
SEND

7
00:01:33,527 --> 00:01:36,071
EMAIL WAS SENT SUCCESSFULLY

8
00:01:42,328 --> 00:01:43,787
MS. JOO IN-A

9
00:01:43,871 --> 00:01:45,122
...AN INAPPROPRIATE
WORKPLACE RELATIONSHIP

10
00:01:45,206 --> 00:01:47,875
HAEMU STRATEGIC PLANNING, MARKETING,
DIGITAL MARKETING, AUDIT TEAM 1, 2, 3

11
00:01:52,379 --> 00:01:55,508
SEND

12
00:02:02,431 --> 00:02:03,474
SECRETARY AHN SEUNG-HEE

13
00:02:06,352 --> 00:02:07,478
- Hey.
- A-jeong.

14
00:02:07,895 --> 00:02:09,647
Check out the article I just sent.

15
00:02:14,693 --> 00:02:17,488
HAEMU'S FIRSTBORN DRIVEN OUT?
SIBLING RIVALRY HEATS UP

16
00:02:18,739 --> 00:02:20,074
Did you call the PR Team?

17
00:02:20,157 --> 00:02:22,952
Look into the journalist
and find out how he got the story.

18
00:02:23,035 --> 00:02:24,286
I'll call Legal.

19
00:02:46,517 --> 00:02:47,518
In-a.

20
00:02:54,650 --> 00:02:57,111
Can I help you?
I'm cleaning the suite.

21
00:02:59,530 --> 00:03:00,614
You can't...

22
00:03:27,224 --> 00:03:28,892
You're gonna burn a hole
through my face.

23
00:03:30,436 --> 00:03:33,897
I know I'm a charming
and good-looking guy, but...

24
00:03:45,993 --> 00:03:47,077
What are you doing?

25
00:03:47,411 --> 00:03:48,579
Checking to see if you're real.

26
00:03:50,748 --> 00:03:53,751
How did you manage to show up
right at that moment?

27
00:03:56,962 --> 00:03:57,963
Unbelievable.

28
00:03:59,256 --> 00:04:00,424
What kind of moment was it?

29
00:04:00,758 --> 00:04:02,718
It was the moment I thought
that I wanted to see you.

30
00:04:07,306 --> 00:04:09,099
How could you say something
so heart-fluttering

31
00:04:10,684 --> 00:04:12,144
with such a straight face?

32
00:04:17,816 --> 00:04:18,942
I was regretting

33
00:04:19,818 --> 00:04:21,403
not being true to my feelings.

34
00:04:23,322 --> 00:04:25,074
I wanted to turn things back

35
00:04:25,699 --> 00:04:26,742
but thought it was too late.

36
00:04:27,368 --> 00:04:29,036
I was upset,
and it left me with regrets.

37
00:04:29,953 --> 00:04:31,163
But at the same time, I thought

38
00:04:31,997 --> 00:04:34,333
"Oh, I'd love to see
Ki-jun right now."

39
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:37,294
Just when I was thinking that,
you appeared out of nowhere.

40
00:04:38,545 --> 00:04:40,089
I kind of knew that feeling

41
00:04:40,923 --> 00:04:43,133
so I rushed here
without wasting a second.

42
00:04:48,722 --> 00:04:50,808
Thank you for coming to get me.

43
00:04:56,897 --> 00:04:59,650
Let's turn things back one by one.

44
00:05:00,484 --> 00:05:01,610
I won't go to the US.

45
00:05:02,069 --> 00:05:03,404
I'm doing whatever it takes to stay.

46
00:05:03,904 --> 00:05:05,322
If you try to force me to go

47
00:05:05,823 --> 00:05:07,741
I'll lie down flat in the lobby
to protest so I can stay.

48
00:05:11,203 --> 00:05:15,708
The thing is, going to the US office
would be a great opportunity for you.

49
00:05:16,417 --> 00:05:18,043
Didn't we agree to be honest?

50
00:05:20,504 --> 00:05:21,839
Should I actually go?

51
00:05:24,341 --> 00:05:26,176
No, don't go.

52
00:05:26,468 --> 00:05:27,678
Stay right next to me.

53
00:05:29,388 --> 00:05:30,431
You bet.

54
00:05:50,701 --> 00:05:53,162
- That's it?
- Yes, that's it.

55
00:05:54,913 --> 00:05:55,998
What about the other side?

56
00:06:37,748 --> 00:06:40,417
What's this?
We only just said goodbye.

57
00:06:40,751 --> 00:06:41,752
Do you miss me already?

58
00:06:42,461 --> 00:06:44,505
Yes, I miss you.

59
00:06:47,758 --> 00:06:49,134
My heart almost burst.

60
00:06:49,426 --> 00:06:50,594
Over that?

61
00:06:51,470 --> 00:06:53,347
You should brace yourself.

62
00:06:53,972 --> 00:06:55,641
Once I start dating someone

63
00:06:55,724 --> 00:06:57,434
I get all passionate and fired up.

64
00:06:58,936 --> 00:07:00,437
I knew it.

65
00:07:00,979 --> 00:07:03,315
I should brace myself
to date someone like you.

66
00:07:05,108 --> 00:07:06,568
I'm not so easygoing either.

67
00:07:06,944 --> 00:07:09,530
So you should brace yourself as well.

68
00:07:09,696 --> 00:07:10,781
What, really?

69
00:07:11,615 --> 00:07:13,158
What should I prepare first?

70
00:07:15,911 --> 00:07:18,080
Why don't we figure out
what to call each other?

71
00:07:18,705 --> 00:07:20,833
I don't want
to have to call you "Ms. Joo."

72
00:07:20,916 --> 00:07:22,251
It's too formal and unfriendly.

73
00:07:24,419 --> 00:07:25,420
My darling In-a.

74
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:27,881
In-a.

75
00:07:28,966 --> 00:07:30,551
Now that I think about it

76
00:07:30,968 --> 00:07:32,427
you have a beautiful name.

77
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:34,763
Joo In-a.

78
00:07:37,307 --> 00:07:39,309
- Hi, guys.
- Hey.

79
00:07:43,021 --> 00:07:44,731
- Let's drink.
- Cheers.

80
00:07:49,862 --> 00:07:52,072
Jae-yeol, what's up with you?

81
00:07:52,155 --> 00:07:53,740
You never joined us
when we invited you before.

82
00:07:55,158 --> 00:07:56,493
I know I was too distant.

83
00:07:57,411 --> 00:07:58,620
Sorry about that.

84
00:07:59,705 --> 00:08:02,749
Hey, I think you should slow down.

85
00:08:02,833 --> 00:08:03,959
Aren't you drinking too much?

86
00:08:05,294 --> 00:08:09,047
Are you getting wasted because
your stepbrother was made co-VP?

87
00:08:09,214 --> 00:08:10,340
I read about that in the news.

88
00:08:10,674 --> 00:08:12,092
Your father's just...

89
00:08:12,676 --> 00:08:16,054
He could've just put things in order
instead of making him co-VP.

90
00:08:16,138 --> 00:08:17,931
It's like he put you two
in a cage to fight.

91
00:08:18,265 --> 00:08:20,642
You talk too much
when we're here to drink.

92
00:08:21,184 --> 00:08:22,811
- Drink up.
- Yes.

93
00:08:23,103 --> 00:08:25,188
Jae-yeol rarely joins us for drinks.

94
00:08:25,439 --> 00:08:27,691
- Let's drink.
- And get wasted.

95
00:09:21,411 --> 00:09:22,412
It's cold, isn't it?

96
00:09:23,413 --> 00:09:24,414
No.

97
00:09:29,753 --> 00:09:31,129
Do you like it that much?

98
00:09:32,047 --> 00:09:33,048
Yes.

99
00:09:35,884 --> 00:09:38,553
I can't believe I look forward
to going to work in the morning.

100
00:09:39,221 --> 00:09:40,222
For real?

101
00:09:40,722 --> 00:09:42,307
I love heading into work.

102
00:09:42,516 --> 00:09:44,685
Work is much more fun
than being bored at home.

103
00:09:45,185 --> 00:09:46,186
No wonder.

104
00:09:47,312 --> 00:09:48,939
You had a look of madness
in your eyes.

105
00:09:51,942 --> 00:09:55,862
We'll do more fun things together
other than just work.

106
00:09:56,697 --> 00:09:58,824
Clear your schedule this weekend.

107
00:09:59,741 --> 00:10:03,996
We went all the way to Jeju Island
but had to return right away.

108
00:10:04,746 --> 00:10:06,331
I booked a pool villa in Sokcho.

109
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:09,668
Let's take our time
to play in the sea

110
00:10:10,127 --> 00:10:11,211
and get some fresh air.

111
00:10:12,796 --> 00:10:14,673
Is this an overnight trip?

112
00:10:19,469 --> 00:10:21,471
It's... Well...

113
00:10:21,763 --> 00:10:23,932
A one-day trip
won't leave us much time.

114
00:10:29,771 --> 00:10:30,856
I love it.

115
00:10:35,944 --> 00:10:37,654
I'm kind of worried

116
00:10:38,488 --> 00:10:40,907
that I won't be able to hide
how much I like you at work.

117
00:10:41,283 --> 00:10:43,368
- What should I do?
- I'd love to see that.

118
00:10:44,161 --> 00:10:45,162
Not being able to hide it.

119
00:10:47,789 --> 00:10:49,082
Don't smile like that.

120
00:10:49,291 --> 00:10:51,460
If you smile, I can't help but smile,
and my feelings will show.

121
00:10:54,838 --> 00:10:57,841
This is a serious matter.
It's going to be too obvious.

122
00:10:58,967 --> 00:11:00,552
Too obvious, my foot.

123
00:11:12,647 --> 00:11:13,982
Even when she's in a relationship

124
00:11:15,609 --> 00:11:19,029
Joo In-a was
still her old self at work.

125
00:11:20,030 --> 00:11:22,282
So what is your conclusion?

126
00:11:22,949 --> 00:11:25,243
It doesn't say on this page
or on this page.

127
00:11:26,453 --> 00:11:28,663
There's nothing.
This report has no key point!

128
00:11:29,623 --> 00:11:30,624
See this?

129
00:11:31,374 --> 00:11:33,460
Do you see a key point
in this report?

130
00:11:35,504 --> 00:11:39,049
This is the kind of report you should
pay to write, not be paid to write.

131
00:11:39,341 --> 00:11:40,383
It's a waste of paper.

132
00:11:41,510 --> 00:11:42,719
Rewrite the whole thing.

133
00:12:06,785 --> 00:12:08,161
Are you all right, Mr. Noh?

134
00:12:09,579 --> 00:12:10,580
Mr. Noh.

135
00:12:10,914 --> 00:12:12,749
Did you do something
to get on her nerves?

136
00:12:13,375 --> 00:12:15,919
No, it's because he's working
too much.

137
00:12:16,586 --> 00:12:18,672
Mr. Noh, be more like me.

138
00:12:19,673 --> 00:12:21,299
Talk more and do less.

139
00:12:21,383 --> 00:12:24,052
The more an auditor does,
the harder they get audited.

140
00:12:24,261 --> 00:12:26,263
The more you do,
the more there is to criticize.

141
00:12:28,014 --> 00:12:29,933
Those are such wise words.

142
00:12:30,475 --> 00:12:32,185
For someone who doesn't do much

143
00:12:32,269 --> 00:12:36,523
how do you end up with the most
overtime pay each month?

144
00:12:36,606 --> 00:12:38,358
Will you all stop it?

145
00:12:38,817 --> 00:12:39,818
Ms. Yoon.

146
00:12:40,235 --> 00:12:42,529
Did you finish the slides
for the presentation on our clubs?

147
00:12:42,612 --> 00:12:45,031
Yes, I emailed you the final version.

148
00:12:45,115 --> 00:12:46,324
Good job.

149
00:12:46,575 --> 00:12:50,245
Did you add as many photos, tables,
and animations as possible?

150
00:12:51,955 --> 00:12:53,707
I'm sure you did your job.

151
00:12:53,790 --> 00:12:54,791
Good for you.

152
00:12:55,125 --> 00:12:58,128
When we present the report
to Ms. Joo later

153
00:12:58,211 --> 00:12:59,588
you're all coming with me.

154
00:13:00,589 --> 00:13:01,631
You, too, Mr. Noh.

155
00:13:02,549 --> 00:13:05,218
Ms. Joo is a really nice person.

156
00:13:05,302 --> 00:13:06,595
Don't be too afraid of her.

157
00:13:07,429 --> 00:13:08,471
Okay.

158
00:13:09,806 --> 00:13:11,391
I'm sure she's a nice person.

159
00:13:17,898 --> 00:13:19,232
The problem is that she's too nice.

160
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:39,961
Ms. Park?

161
00:13:41,630 --> 00:13:45,258
- Yes?
- When will VP Jeon be here?

162
00:13:46,092 --> 00:13:48,678
He isn't well today.

163
00:13:50,013 --> 00:13:52,515
I'll present the agenda instead.

164
00:13:56,728 --> 00:13:57,729
Okay.

165
00:13:58,480 --> 00:14:00,607
We can't wait forever.

166
00:14:08,490 --> 00:14:09,658
Let's start without him.

167
00:14:10,367 --> 00:14:13,245
Don't you forget
that I am a VP as well.

168
00:14:14,079 --> 00:14:16,706
Yes, I think
it would be fine to start.

169
00:14:17,415 --> 00:14:19,167
Ms. Park, you can leave.

170
00:14:19,251 --> 00:14:20,710
- But...
- Being a secretary

171
00:14:21,044 --> 00:14:24,047
doesn't give you the right
to attend in a VP's place.

172
00:14:41,314 --> 00:14:44,234
VICE PRESIDENT

173
00:14:47,445 --> 00:14:49,656
SECRETARY PARK A-JEONG

174
00:15:45,628 --> 00:15:48,381
- Gosh, the water...
- It's so clear.

175
00:15:49,466 --> 00:15:51,551
Were they rockfish? Did you see them?

176
00:15:51,634 --> 00:15:52,761
- Yes.
- There was a swarm.

177
00:15:52,844 --> 00:15:54,929
- It was amazing.
- Just fantastic.

178
00:15:55,513 --> 00:15:56,639
- Did you notice?
- Yes.

179
00:15:56,723 --> 00:15:58,016
- Right?
- Did you?

180
00:15:58,099 --> 00:15:59,392
- I saw.
- What was that?

181
00:16:00,226 --> 00:16:01,394
It was incredible.

182
00:16:01,895 --> 00:16:03,146
The water's so clear today.

183
00:16:03,438 --> 00:16:05,148
- It's a rare occasion.
- I know.

184
00:16:11,488 --> 00:16:12,864
- You're back.
- Yes.

185
00:16:13,281 --> 00:16:14,324
Did you have fun?

186
00:16:14,991 --> 00:16:16,242
Is Seo-yeon in bed?

187
00:16:16,534 --> 00:16:17,535
Yes.

188
00:16:18,703 --> 00:16:21,748
Her English kindergarten is hosting
a cooking class on the 29th.

189
00:16:21,831 --> 00:16:22,957
You can make it, right?

190
00:16:28,171 --> 00:16:30,173
- I have a club meeting on the 29th.
- Again?

191
00:16:30,632 --> 00:16:32,967
Why do you have to go
scuba diving that often?

192
00:16:35,887 --> 00:16:37,639
Can't you miss it for once?

193
00:16:38,181 --> 00:16:40,809
I went on my own
to Seo-yeon's speech contest.

194
00:16:40,892 --> 00:16:42,644
Do you know how upset she was
that you'd missed it?

195
00:16:42,727 --> 00:16:45,188
I'll be at the next one.

196
00:16:47,190 --> 00:16:48,983
Are you sure you go scuba diving?

197
00:16:49,692 --> 00:16:51,111
Are you up to something else?

198
00:17:08,420 --> 00:17:09,462
AUDIT SUMMARY

199
00:17:09,921 --> 00:17:14,426
We found four cases in which
clubs fraudulently enrolled

200
00:17:14,509 --> 00:17:18,054
new recruits or temporary staff
to collect extra club funds.

201
00:17:18,138 --> 00:17:21,641
And in seven cases,
club admin embezzled club funds

202
00:17:21,724 --> 00:17:24,477
rented spaces or paid instructors
for personal gain.

203
00:17:25,937 --> 00:17:28,231
We found eight malpractice cases
where club members

204
00:17:28,314 --> 00:17:30,900
hired businesses
run by friends or family.

205
00:17:30,984 --> 00:17:34,362
In two cases, there were issues
that constituted gambling.

206
00:17:36,406 --> 00:17:38,867
The in-house clubs currently hand in

207
00:17:38,950 --> 00:17:41,828
- an activity report yearly, right?
- Yes, that's right.

208
00:17:41,911 --> 00:17:45,665
Have them submit one each quarter
with more details in the report.

209
00:17:45,748 --> 00:17:47,041
Ask HR to make the announcement.

210
00:17:47,125 --> 00:17:48,751
Okay, I'll relay the message.

211
00:17:48,835 --> 00:17:51,921
We also have a club-related PM case.

212
00:17:53,798 --> 00:17:56,843
The wife of Min Tae-woo
at Haemu International contacted us.

213
00:17:56,926 --> 00:18:00,013
Her husband is way too active
in the scuba diving club.

214
00:18:00,096 --> 00:18:02,307
She's not entirely sure
their activities are wholesome.

215
00:18:02,390 --> 00:18:06,603
It's hard to tell because of the gear
but the man on the right is Mr. Min.

216
00:18:06,686 --> 00:18:09,814
The person on the right is
suspected to be his affair partner.

217
00:18:09,898 --> 00:18:12,567
The wife found many photos
of this person in particular.

218
00:18:12,650 --> 00:18:14,402
Aren't they just enjoying a hobby?

219
00:18:14,486 --> 00:18:16,196
It did seem somewhat odd.

220
00:18:16,279 --> 00:18:18,907
Mr. Min supposedly dislikes water
and didn't even swim.

221
00:18:18,990 --> 00:18:21,910
He goes scuba diving
almost every week now.

222
00:18:21,993 --> 00:18:24,370
He's known to even
take time off work to go.

223
00:18:24,454 --> 00:18:26,706
And at home,
he always says he's tired.

224
00:18:26,789 --> 00:18:29,501
Oh, and he gets calls at dawn
or in the middle of the night

225
00:18:29,584 --> 00:18:31,252
and jumps up to go out.

226
00:18:31,336 --> 00:18:34,339
Many complain
that company clubs foster affairs

227
00:18:34,422 --> 00:18:37,884
and that the company encourages it
by covering expenses.

228
00:18:37,967 --> 00:18:40,970
Why don't we make this an example
and look into this incident?

229
00:18:41,054 --> 00:18:43,932
We won't get anywhere
with what we have if they deny it.

230
00:18:46,184 --> 00:18:49,395
Let's attend a club outing
and see how things actually are.

231
00:18:51,064 --> 00:18:52,190
Mr. Noh.

232
00:18:52,607 --> 00:18:53,983
Do you know how to scuba-dive?

233
00:18:55,527 --> 00:18:57,904
I did take a few lessons
on a trip once.

234
00:18:57,987 --> 00:18:59,864
You should go to Mr. Min's club

235
00:18:59,948 --> 00:19:01,032
- this weekend.
- What?

236
00:19:04,661 --> 00:19:06,412
This weekend

237
00:19:07,830 --> 00:19:10,333
I have an important appointment.

238
00:19:12,377 --> 00:19:13,378
Do you?

239
00:19:14,337 --> 00:19:16,965
Is anyone else able to scuba-dive?

240
00:19:17,549 --> 00:19:19,676
Extended exposure to water
gives me a rash.

241
00:19:19,759 --> 00:19:21,010
- The sea...
- That's bad.

242
00:19:21,094 --> 00:19:23,429
I almost drowned in a river
as a child and the trauma...

243
00:19:23,513 --> 00:19:25,431
- I can't equalize underwater.
- I can't manage.

244
00:19:25,515 --> 00:19:27,225
I refuse to work on weekends.

245
00:19:27,308 --> 00:19:29,185
It verges on a rare disease.

246
00:19:29,894 --> 00:19:31,229
Oh, dear...

247
00:19:31,938 --> 00:19:33,439
I'm left with no choice, then.

248
00:19:34,190 --> 00:19:35,692
I love scuba diving.

249
00:19:36,901 --> 00:19:38,444
- I'll go.
- What?

250
00:19:38,528 --> 00:19:39,571
What?

251
00:19:45,868 --> 00:19:47,662
Don't you have anything planned

252
00:19:48,371 --> 00:19:50,290
for this weekend?

253
00:19:50,373 --> 00:19:52,750
I don't have
any special plans this weekend.

254
00:19:53,418 --> 00:19:55,044
Clear your schedule this weekend.

255
00:19:55,128 --> 00:19:56,796
I booked a pool villa in Sokcho.

256
00:19:56,879 --> 00:19:58,423
I thought I didn't have plans.

257
00:20:02,468 --> 00:20:03,886
You do have plans, then.

258
00:20:04,721 --> 00:20:06,347
How could you?

259
00:20:07,432 --> 00:20:10,643
Aren't you happy
we get to travel together?

260
00:20:11,269 --> 00:20:13,688
We're doing
exactly what we planned to do.

261
00:20:13,771 --> 00:20:15,106
We see the sea
and get some fresh air.

262
00:20:15,189 --> 00:20:16,733
- Plus, we get to work, too.
- Goodness.

263
00:20:16,816 --> 00:20:17,984
We hit two birds with one stone

264
00:20:18,067 --> 00:20:20,028
by going swimming
and seeing some fish.

265
00:20:20,111 --> 00:20:23,364
You said you get passionate
when you start dating.

266
00:20:23,448 --> 00:20:25,199
But all you did was
make me work passionately.

267
00:20:25,283 --> 00:20:27,785
I thought I was going
to burn to ashes with your passion.

268
00:20:27,869 --> 00:20:29,954
That was because we had a lot to do

269
00:20:30,038 --> 00:20:31,664
because of the previous week's trip.

270
00:20:31,748 --> 00:20:34,584
Also, I didn't want anyone at work
to notice anything.

271
00:20:34,792 --> 00:20:36,127
I put on an act with a poker face.

272
00:20:36,210 --> 00:20:38,880
You got so into that act
that you forgot our weekend plan.

273
00:20:40,882 --> 00:20:43,718
That was because it's been so long
since I made weekend plans.

274
00:20:44,385 --> 00:20:45,637
Plus, this is work.

275
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:47,972
I'm very good at separating
work from my personal life.

276
00:20:48,056 --> 00:20:49,932
Yes, of course. I get it, Ms. Joo.

277
00:20:50,350 --> 00:20:52,769
We're on a business trip,
not a pleasure cruise.

278
00:20:52,852 --> 00:20:55,647
I'll make sure to act accordingly,
completely aloof and official.

279
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:00,526
Ki-jun, are you actually angry?

280
00:21:01,402 --> 00:21:02,445
Yes.

281
00:21:04,072 --> 00:21:06,324
You fool. You twit.

282
00:21:06,574 --> 00:21:08,868
How could you forget your first date?

283
00:21:09,160 --> 00:21:10,912
- Get a grip, In-a!
- Don't.

284
00:21:10,995 --> 00:21:12,497
- What are you doing?
- What?

285
00:21:12,580 --> 00:21:13,790
I deserve a good scolding.

286
00:21:13,873 --> 00:21:17,335
- You fool. You twit. You moron.
- No, stop it. Don't do that.

287
00:21:17,418 --> 00:21:19,379
I was kidding, okay?

288
00:21:19,671 --> 00:21:21,506
I'm not angry at all. I was joking.

289
00:21:21,589 --> 00:21:23,883
- You seemed really angry.
- I wasn't.

290
00:21:23,966 --> 00:21:25,468
I wasn't even sulking.

291
00:21:26,052 --> 00:21:27,553
I'm really sorry.

292
00:21:28,012 --> 00:21:29,138
Don't be.

293
00:21:29,931 --> 00:21:31,474
Goodness...

294
00:21:37,063 --> 00:21:40,191
We have new members joining us today.

295
00:21:40,358 --> 00:21:43,319
It's Ms. Joo In-a, Head of Audit
from the head office

296
00:21:43,403 --> 00:21:45,822
and Assistant Manager Noh Ki-jun.

297
00:21:46,572 --> 00:21:48,991
- It's a pleasure to meet you all.
- Applause.

298
00:21:49,742 --> 00:21:51,828
You're both from the Audit Team

299
00:21:51,911 --> 00:21:53,705
so I feel somewhat nervous.

300
00:21:53,788 --> 00:21:57,959
We use our funds appropriately
and we do nothing wrong, do we?

301
00:21:58,042 --> 00:21:59,502
- Do you all agree?
- Yes.

302
00:21:59,585 --> 00:22:02,255
Club president, don't you know
saying that makes you look guilty?

303
00:22:03,005 --> 00:22:04,215
You have a point.

304
00:22:04,298 --> 00:22:07,844
We have a small group today,
so we'll go out together.

305
00:22:07,927 --> 00:22:09,846
Check your equipment thoroughly.

306
00:22:09,929 --> 00:22:11,097
- Okay.
- Okay.

307
00:22:11,305 --> 00:22:12,432
Get to it.

308
00:22:18,104 --> 00:22:19,313
Hey.

309
00:22:35,913 --> 00:22:36,998
Watch out.

310
00:22:37,081 --> 00:22:39,500
This valve here needs to be checked.

311
00:22:40,418 --> 00:22:42,086
We run on a buddy system.

312
00:22:42,170 --> 00:22:43,713
This is your first dive with us

313
00:22:43,796 --> 00:22:46,090
so you should partner
with someone more experienced.

314
00:22:46,340 --> 00:22:49,302
I will partner with Mr. Min, then.

315
00:22:49,469 --> 00:22:52,597
The way he's helping her
looks reliable and reassuring.

316
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:55,558
Then Mr. Min, you'll go out with him.

317
00:22:55,641 --> 00:22:57,393
- Okay.
- Ms. Joo, your partner...

318
00:22:57,477 --> 00:22:58,644
I volunteer.

319
00:23:22,126 --> 00:23:24,128
Mr. Min and Ms. Ha seem pretty close.

320
00:23:24,754 --> 00:23:26,255
Yes, they do.

321
00:23:28,466 --> 00:23:30,843
Are you upset Ms. Ha
is his possible fling?

322
00:23:31,302 --> 00:23:32,345
What?

323
00:23:33,012 --> 00:23:36,474
You couldn't seem to take
your eyes off her.

324
00:23:36,557 --> 00:23:39,519
What does that mean work-wise?

325
00:23:40,520 --> 00:23:43,523
My eyes were not locked onto her.

326
00:23:44,649 --> 00:23:46,192
It's all work-related.

327
00:23:46,567 --> 00:23:50,738
I just wanted to confirm if she was
the other person in the photos.

328
00:23:51,864 --> 00:23:52,865
I'll see you later.

329
00:23:55,201 --> 00:23:56,327
Personal-wise.

330
00:24:00,414 --> 00:24:01,541
Gosh...

331
00:24:02,041 --> 00:24:04,544
Get ready to dive.
Get your equipment.

332
00:24:04,627 --> 00:24:05,711
- Okay.
- Okay.

333
00:24:06,462 --> 00:24:07,630
Be sure to check that.

334
00:24:08,714 --> 00:24:10,216
- Okay, checked.
- Good.

335
00:24:10,716 --> 00:24:12,468
- It's all done.
- Great.

336
00:26:33,526 --> 00:26:35,152
Are you all right?

337
00:26:47,289 --> 00:26:49,208
That seemed like a panic attack.

338
00:26:50,334 --> 00:26:52,420
Are you claustrophobic or something?

339
00:26:53,045 --> 00:26:55,423
I'm fine. It wasn't anything serious.

340
00:26:55,506 --> 00:26:57,091
Did you tell the instructor?

341
00:26:57,550 --> 00:27:00,803
You should inform the others
for their safety, too.

342
00:27:00,886 --> 00:27:02,346
It's not that serious, okay?

343
00:27:04,390 --> 00:27:09,729
Are you afraid you won't get to dive
if the others find out about this?

344
00:27:10,229 --> 00:27:11,647
Do you love to dive that much?

345
00:27:11,731 --> 00:27:14,108
You say too much
for someone who just joined.

346
00:27:14,734 --> 00:27:16,235
I can handle my business.

347
00:27:17,570 --> 00:27:18,863
Stay out of it.

348
00:27:36,589 --> 00:27:37,757
Oh, come on.

349
00:27:38,007 --> 00:27:39,425
It was a great dive.

350
00:27:40,551 --> 00:27:44,764
He braves panic attacks to dive
just so he can see a woman regularly?

351
00:27:45,806 --> 00:27:48,142
He could if he likes her that much.

352
00:27:48,225 --> 00:27:50,728
It makes for a good excuse
for them to spend time together.

353
00:27:52,521 --> 00:27:54,648
Ms. Ha is a veteran diver.

354
00:27:55,524 --> 00:27:57,526
This story makes more sense.

355
00:27:57,610 --> 00:27:59,236
Mr. Min fell for Ms. Ha first

356
00:27:59,320 --> 00:28:01,697
found out what her hobby was,
and joined the club.

357
00:28:03,866 --> 00:28:06,118
Gosh, if that's true

358
00:28:07,369 --> 00:28:09,038
he's risking his life
for just an affair.

359
00:28:10,122 --> 00:28:12,792
I'm so sorry about this.
I'd love to join you for dinner

360
00:28:12,875 --> 00:28:15,461
but I have to get back to attend
an old coworker's father's funeral.

361
00:28:15,544 --> 00:28:17,755
I had a great time today.
See you on the next dive.

362
00:28:17,838 --> 00:28:19,090
- Goodbye.
- Get back safely.

363
00:28:19,173 --> 00:28:20,925
- Bye.
- Sleep well.

364
00:28:21,008 --> 00:28:22,093
- Bye.
- Goodbye.

365
00:28:22,593 --> 00:28:23,969
What do we eat for dinner?

366
00:28:24,053 --> 00:28:26,097
We had so much fun
swimming with the fish.

367
00:28:26,180 --> 00:28:28,140
We're not eating raw fish, are we?

368
00:28:29,141 --> 00:28:30,476
How about a toast?

369
00:28:30,893 --> 00:28:32,895
- Good dive!
- Good dive!

370
00:28:32,978 --> 00:28:34,730
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

371
00:28:41,487 --> 00:28:43,114
They were friends only moments ago.

372
00:28:44,657 --> 00:28:45,866
Goodbye, little fishies.

373
00:28:48,494 --> 00:28:51,247
Ms. Joo is hilarious.
Don't you think?

374
00:28:54,375 --> 00:28:57,837
These aren't the fish we saw,
so there's no need to feel bad.

375
00:28:58,212 --> 00:28:59,880
The ssamjang here is the best.

376
00:29:00,548 --> 00:29:02,049
Here we go. Open up.

377
00:29:07,471 --> 00:29:08,639
Is it good?

378
00:29:13,686 --> 00:29:15,229
Mr. Noh, you, too. Open up.

379
00:29:16,981 --> 00:29:19,024
- What?
- Don't be shy.

380
00:29:19,358 --> 00:29:20,693
Open your mouth wide.

381
00:29:30,661 --> 00:29:32,246
That tastes amazing.

382
00:29:32,872 --> 00:29:35,124
Ms. Ha, your wraps are the best.

383
00:29:35,207 --> 00:29:37,751
Who taught you the recipe?

384
00:29:38,627 --> 00:29:39,712
It's so good.

385
00:30:05,613 --> 00:30:07,823
He drank enough alcohol
to kill himself.

386
00:30:08,449 --> 00:30:09,658
If you were any later

387
00:30:10,701 --> 00:30:11,994
something terrible could've happened.

388
00:30:39,772 --> 00:30:40,981
That's not going to happen.

389
00:30:42,608 --> 00:30:44,276
We can't go back
to how things used to be.

390
00:30:47,279 --> 00:30:48,364
What I'm trying to say is

391
00:30:49,823 --> 00:30:51,951
I'm never going back to you,
Jae-yeol.

392
00:31:07,841 --> 00:31:09,885
OUR DEEPEST CONDOLENCES

393
00:31:09,969 --> 00:31:11,804
MAY HE REST IN PEACE

394
00:31:14,682 --> 00:31:16,934
Are you recruitment peers
with Mr. Lee, then?

395
00:31:17,017 --> 00:31:18,477
He's one of the few guys
from the same batch.

396
00:31:18,560 --> 00:31:20,813
Right. You realize
that when you're at work

397
00:31:20,896 --> 00:31:22,898
your recruitment peer is
the closest you have to a friend.

398
00:31:22,982 --> 00:31:24,692
All my peers retired early

399
00:31:24,775 --> 00:31:26,193
- and recently, one...
- Mr. Han.

400
00:31:26,277 --> 00:31:28,195
- Long time no see.
- Hi, take a seat.

401
00:31:28,279 --> 00:31:30,197
- Hello.
- Let me introduce him, Mr. Moo.

402
00:31:30,281 --> 00:31:33,158
This is Yoon Sang-ho from Haemu
International Global Business Team.

403
00:31:33,742 --> 00:31:35,494
This is Audit Team's Leader
Moo Kwang-il.

404
00:31:35,577 --> 00:31:36,912
- It's a pleasure.
- Same here.

405
00:31:36,996 --> 00:31:38,956
I met two others
from your team today.

406
00:31:39,039 --> 00:31:41,792
I just got back
from the Scuba Diving Club

407
00:31:41,875 --> 00:31:45,879
and your head Ms. Joo
and Mr. Noh were there.

408
00:31:45,963 --> 00:31:47,756
- Oh, I see.
- Yes.

409
00:31:47,840 --> 00:31:50,551
- Let me pour you one.
- No, I drove here.

410
00:31:50,634 --> 00:31:52,386
- I'll pour you one instead.
- What a pity.

411
00:31:52,469 --> 00:31:54,555
- Not at all.
- Didn't you drive here

412
00:31:54,638 --> 00:31:57,891
- if you just got back from a trip?
- I can always hire a driver.

413
00:31:57,975 --> 00:31:59,852
- It's an honor to meet you.
- Same here.

414
00:32:04,315 --> 00:32:05,899
What's up with Ms. Ha?

415
00:32:06,608 --> 00:32:08,569
She stuck close to Mr. Min

416
00:32:09,028 --> 00:32:11,238
but then
she seemed interested in you, too.

417
00:32:11,572 --> 00:32:16,368
Well, I'm usually at the center
of everyone's attention.

418
00:32:16,452 --> 00:32:19,246
Is she the type who wants to get
all the men's attention?

419
00:32:20,914 --> 00:32:23,751
It's not all men, but me.

420
00:32:24,585 --> 00:32:26,086
It's because I'm Noh Ki-jun.

421
00:32:27,880 --> 00:32:29,256
It's Min and Ha.

422
00:32:36,221 --> 00:32:40,768
He's loading her equipment
into his car, isn't he?

423
00:32:42,061 --> 00:32:43,687
Something's up with them.

424
00:32:54,114 --> 00:32:55,115
Wait.

425
00:32:55,991 --> 00:32:57,451
Is he driving off with the equipment?

426
00:32:58,660 --> 00:32:59,661
Yes.

427
00:32:59,745 --> 00:33:02,456
It looks like Mr. Min
got a call from someone.

428
00:33:05,125 --> 00:33:06,210
Where's Ms. Ha?

429
00:33:23,685 --> 00:33:25,396
I'm really sorry.

430
00:33:25,479 --> 00:33:27,981
I get carsick easily
and can't sit in the back.

431
00:33:28,816 --> 00:33:31,026
Plus, that's usually
where the boss sits, right?

432
00:33:31,652 --> 00:33:32,861
You're the boss.

433
00:33:33,654 --> 00:33:35,322
I appreciate that.

434
00:33:35,406 --> 00:33:36,740
By the way...

435
00:33:37,491 --> 00:33:39,493
Where do you live, Mr. Noh?

436
00:33:39,743 --> 00:33:41,870
- What?
- Do you live nearby?

437
00:33:42,913 --> 00:33:46,250
I hope you don't have to make
too long a detour.

438
00:33:46,333 --> 00:33:48,168
I don't. It's fine.

439
00:33:49,878 --> 00:33:50,921
I have a question.

440
00:33:53,507 --> 00:33:57,094
Don't you dislike joining a club
with your direct superior?

441
00:33:57,177 --> 00:33:58,679
Oh, gosh. I can hear every word.

442
00:33:59,555 --> 00:34:01,014
My bad.

443
00:34:02,182 --> 00:34:04,393
Our dear Mr. Min's having a hard time

444
00:34:04,476 --> 00:34:08,021
because his superior Mr. Yoon
is in the same club.

445
00:34:14,278 --> 00:34:17,865
You and Mr. Min must be really close.

446
00:34:18,574 --> 00:34:20,701
You talked so much earlier today

447
00:34:20,784 --> 00:34:23,704
and just now you called him
"our dear Mr. Min."

448
00:34:24,496 --> 00:34:25,539
Oh, gosh.

449
00:34:27,291 --> 00:34:28,625
You got the wrong idea.

450
00:34:30,043 --> 00:34:32,880
Mr. Min's married with a kid.

451
00:34:33,213 --> 00:34:34,756
We're second cousins.

452
00:34:35,466 --> 00:34:37,384
It's a pure coincidence
that we joined the same club.

453
00:34:38,218 --> 00:34:40,512
Then you and Mr. Min

454
00:34:41,054 --> 00:34:42,639
are just relatives?

455
00:34:42,973 --> 00:34:46,518
Yes, that's why I loaded
my equipment in his trunk.

456
00:34:47,561 --> 00:34:49,897
Wait, what? Are you serious?

457
00:34:50,230 --> 00:34:51,899
Where did you get that idea?

458
00:34:52,858 --> 00:34:56,361
Hey, you must
be working out, Mr. Noh.

459
00:34:56,445 --> 00:34:58,655
Gosh, that's just hilarious.

460
00:34:58,739 --> 00:35:00,782
I almost got the wrong idea
about you two.

461
00:35:00,866 --> 00:35:03,702
It's so funny how things may seem.

462
00:35:03,785 --> 00:35:05,078
Goodness...

463
00:35:10,751 --> 00:35:13,378
So in the end, that new recruit

464
00:35:13,462 --> 00:35:16,548
raided HR and made a huge fuss,
which resulted in

465
00:35:16,632 --> 00:35:19,843
kicking out Mr. Lee
to another branch.

466
00:35:19,927 --> 00:35:23,013
These days,
people call everything gaslighting.

467
00:35:23,096 --> 00:35:24,515
We can't even talk anymore.

468
00:35:24,598 --> 00:35:26,558
These kids only learned
the worst in everything.

469
00:35:26,642 --> 00:35:28,727
I'm sure there was a situation...

470
00:35:28,810 --> 00:35:30,729
It doesn't matter
what the situation is.

471
00:35:30,812 --> 00:35:33,899
How dare some rookie dare
to kick the department head out?

472
00:35:33,982 --> 00:35:35,317
How can this happen?

473
00:35:35,567 --> 00:35:38,529
Mr. Moo, if this happened in the army

474
00:35:38,612 --> 00:35:42,324
it'd be like a private messing
with the division commander. Jeez.

475
00:35:42,407 --> 00:35:44,868
Well, the office
isn't the same as the army.

476
00:35:45,118 --> 00:35:46,954
I mean, are they any different?

477
00:35:47,037 --> 00:35:48,872
They're both organizations,
and there are ranks.

478
00:35:48,956 --> 00:35:52,292
If so, we must also establish
proper discipline.

479
00:35:52,376 --> 00:35:54,670
That's what I'm trying to say.

480
00:35:54,753 --> 00:35:58,882
I thought you'd be more open-minded
because you're called the Global Team

481
00:35:58,966 --> 00:36:01,301
but you're even more old-fashioned
than a Korean Audit Team.

482
00:36:01,718 --> 00:36:03,178
Well, old-fashioned?

483
00:36:03,262 --> 00:36:05,889
When we have team dinners,
we don't even drink regular soju.

484
00:36:05,973 --> 00:36:08,642
We only get the red caps,
the ones with more alcohol content.

485
00:36:09,726 --> 00:36:10,936
Goodness, look at the time.

486
00:36:11,019 --> 00:36:12,729
- Please excuse me. Okay?
- You're leaving?

487
00:36:12,813 --> 00:36:15,065
Yes, I'll leave
after saying goodbye to Mr. Lee.

488
00:36:15,148 --> 00:36:16,608
- Eat up, then.
- Thanks.

489
00:36:16,692 --> 00:36:18,652
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

490
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:23,282
- Hello.
- At our club today...

491
00:36:23,365 --> 00:36:25,075
I told you to learn
how to scuba dive, didn't I?

492
00:36:25,158 --> 00:36:27,828
I became acquainted
with the famous Head of Audit

493
00:36:27,911 --> 00:36:29,246
Joo In-a, and met everyone.

494
00:36:29,329 --> 00:36:31,331
I'll introduce her to you soon.

495
00:36:31,999 --> 00:36:34,042
Mr. Moo isn't too resourceful.

496
00:36:34,126 --> 00:36:35,919
There's no way
he's becoming an executive.

497
00:36:36,712 --> 00:36:38,589
But he's a good man.

498
00:36:38,672 --> 00:36:40,841
My friend, there's no use
in living as a good man.

499
00:36:43,176 --> 00:36:44,511
Anyway, one second.

500
00:36:45,345 --> 00:36:46,680
Hey, did you arrive?

501
00:36:47,097 --> 00:36:49,766
Yes, okay. Come to the car. Okay.

502
00:36:50,100 --> 00:36:53,020
- Sorry, my chauffeur's here.
- Okay. Bye.

503
00:36:55,105 --> 00:37:00,152
Jeez. It was awful to listen to him
badmouth people for hours.

504
00:37:03,071 --> 00:37:04,698
Wait. That's...

505
00:37:05,365 --> 00:37:06,992
That's Mr. Min
from the Scuba Diving Club.

506
00:37:08,076 --> 00:37:09,453
Is he waiting for someone?

507
00:37:18,378 --> 00:37:19,504
What?

508
00:37:20,005 --> 00:37:22,674
The chauffeur service Mr. Yoon called
was actually Mr. Min?

509
00:37:23,091 --> 00:37:24,217
Not a hire?

510
00:37:25,010 --> 00:37:26,470
Goodness, that guy.

511
00:37:27,596 --> 00:37:30,307
See? I knew it the moment
he badmouthed those people.

512
00:37:31,016 --> 00:37:32,851
What an awful man.

513
00:37:36,188 --> 00:37:37,481
Mr. Noh, it's me.

514
00:37:37,564 --> 00:37:39,399
I'm calling
about Mr. Yoon of the Global Team.

515
00:37:39,483 --> 00:37:40,859
He's an awful man.

516
00:37:52,537 --> 00:37:53,664
Mr. Yoon.

517
00:37:54,623 --> 00:37:56,375
- Mr. Yoon.
- Man.

518
00:37:57,042 --> 00:37:58,794
I had too much to drink.

519
00:37:59,211 --> 00:38:00,379
One moment.

520
00:38:06,677 --> 00:38:07,886
Gosh.

521
00:38:15,894 --> 00:38:17,187
- I got it.
- Yes, sir.

522
00:38:18,146 --> 00:38:19,981
- And the key. One second.
- Right.

523
00:38:21,692 --> 00:38:22,901
You should have this hangover cure.

524
00:38:22,984 --> 00:38:25,320
Man, that's my Native Speaker.

525
00:38:25,404 --> 00:38:26,446
You're right on.

526
00:38:33,662 --> 00:38:35,580
- Native Speaker.
- Yes, sir.

527
00:38:35,664 --> 00:38:37,624
I've got your back until the very end

528
00:38:37,708 --> 00:38:39,209
so just trust and follow me.

529
00:38:39,292 --> 00:38:42,003
You know I'm the only one who
looks after you in the office, right?

530
00:38:42,087 --> 00:38:43,463
Yes, of course.

531
00:38:43,839 --> 00:38:46,216
I'm always grateful for you.

532
00:38:46,800 --> 00:38:48,677
- Give me. And go.
- Yes, sir.

533
00:38:51,388 --> 00:38:52,472
Mr. Yoon.

534
00:38:53,890 --> 00:38:54,933
Well...

535
00:38:55,350 --> 00:38:57,519
About the diving schedule
next Saturday.

536
00:38:57,936 --> 00:38:58,937
What?

537
00:38:59,646 --> 00:39:01,606
- You can't come?
- Well, it's my kid.

538
00:39:02,399 --> 00:39:04,776
- The kindergarten has a class...
- Hey.

539
00:39:04,860 --> 00:39:06,611
Who am I going to team up with, then?

540
00:39:06,695 --> 00:39:09,948
I was really pissed partnering up
with that punk, the club president.

541
00:39:10,031 --> 00:39:11,783
He'd stop me
from going anywhere I want to

542
00:39:11,867 --> 00:39:14,286
and ring the bell
whenever I try to grab something.

543
00:39:14,369 --> 00:39:17,581
So? Is it too big a burden
to go diving with me every week?

544
00:39:17,664 --> 00:39:18,665
Am I forcing you?

545
00:39:18,749 --> 00:39:20,333
No, Mr. Yoon. That's not the case.

546
00:39:21,042 --> 00:39:22,919
Thanks to you,
I get to enjoy a wonderful hobby.

547
00:39:23,920 --> 00:39:25,088
Yes, kid.

548
00:39:25,881 --> 00:39:27,507
So just follow my footsteps, okay?

549
00:39:27,758 --> 00:39:30,302
You need to get promoted to manager
this time, don't you?

550
00:39:30,385 --> 00:39:32,345
You're the last one
among your recruitment peers.

551
00:39:33,305 --> 00:39:34,681
Yes, you're right.

552
00:39:35,515 --> 00:39:36,808
I'll try even harder.

553
00:39:36,892 --> 00:39:39,311
Don't just try hard, you punk.

554
00:39:40,103 --> 00:39:41,646
Do it well.

555
00:39:43,273 --> 00:39:45,066
Yes, sir. I'll do it well.

556
00:39:45,150 --> 00:39:46,777
Good, Native Speaker.

557
00:39:47,360 --> 00:39:49,070
- Go, now.
- Yes. Goodnight, sir.

558
00:39:49,154 --> 00:39:50,155
Yeah.

559
00:40:03,502 --> 00:40:04,711
Mr. Min.

560
00:40:14,012 --> 00:40:16,598
I heard Mr. Yoon calling you
"Native Speaker."

561
00:40:17,057 --> 00:40:18,391
What does he mean by that?

562
00:40:18,475 --> 00:40:21,686
Everyone in my team has been abroad
except for me.

563
00:40:22,187 --> 00:40:23,939
So they say
I'm the native Korean speaker

564
00:40:24,314 --> 00:40:25,690
and nicknamed me Native Speaker.

565
00:40:29,236 --> 00:40:31,488
It doesn't sound like
a pleasant nickname.

566
00:40:31,863 --> 00:40:34,241
Mr. Min, we saw it all.

567
00:40:34,574 --> 00:40:36,576
We saw you acting
as Mr. Yoon's designated driver.

568
00:40:37,285 --> 00:40:39,830
And you don't like scuba diving

569
00:40:40,038 --> 00:40:41,498
yet you continue doing it
to serve him.

570
00:40:41,581 --> 00:40:43,542
It's just office politics.

571
00:40:43,959 --> 00:40:45,502
Everyone does this.

572
00:40:45,585 --> 00:40:46,753
No, Mr. Min.

573
00:40:47,295 --> 00:40:49,381
That's considered
workplace harassment.

574
00:40:50,257 --> 00:40:51,341
She's right.

575
00:40:51,675 --> 00:40:54,344
You should use this chance
to speak up honestly.

576
00:40:55,220 --> 00:40:57,097
- Even to your wife.
- To my wife?

577
00:40:58,515 --> 00:41:00,433
No, that is something I cannot do.

578
00:41:00,517 --> 00:41:03,436
Your wife took this the wrong way
and thinks you're having an affair.

579
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:05,272
I'd rather live
with the misunderstanding.

580
00:41:05,355 --> 00:41:06,356
Sorry?

581
00:41:07,482 --> 00:41:09,651
I don't want my wife to find out

582
00:41:11,903 --> 00:41:13,822
that this is
how I'm being treated at work.

583
00:41:14,865 --> 00:41:16,116
Right...

584
00:41:26,251 --> 00:41:27,294
I don't think

585
00:41:28,169 --> 00:41:30,338
this is a matter we can let slide.

586
00:41:30,422 --> 00:41:32,340
This isn't just a power dynamic.

587
00:41:32,424 --> 00:41:33,842
It's gaslighting.

588
00:41:33,925 --> 00:41:36,636
I can also understand why
he doesn't want his family to know.

589
00:41:36,720 --> 00:41:39,097
Let's just tell his wife
that we confirmed that

590
00:41:39,180 --> 00:41:40,223
he isn't having an affair.

591
00:41:40,974 --> 00:41:41,975
Okay.

592
00:41:42,058 --> 00:41:43,977
Also, it looks like Mr. Min

593
00:41:44,060 --> 00:41:46,396
needs to be separated
from Mr. Yoon as soon as possible.

594
00:41:47,105 --> 00:41:48,857
I'll try to think of a way.

595
00:41:51,359 --> 00:41:54,613
This isn't something
he can handle personally.

596
00:41:55,906 --> 00:41:58,325
There must be something
that the company can do.

597
00:42:11,171 --> 00:42:13,381
VNow, we're home.

598
00:42:14,174 --> 00:42:15,717
Time to stop thinking today.

599
00:42:15,800 --> 00:42:17,177
Go home and get some rest.

600
00:42:17,385 --> 00:42:19,137
You must be tired
after diving early in the morning.

601
00:42:20,847 --> 00:42:21,932
Mr. Noh.

602
00:42:24,017 --> 00:42:25,310
Do you want to stay for ramyeon?

603
00:42:48,208 --> 00:42:49,542
That's three minutes.

604
00:42:50,585 --> 00:42:53,046
Now, take a break
and have some ramyeon.

605
00:42:54,172 --> 00:42:55,298
Hey, wait.

606
00:42:55,382 --> 00:42:58,635
Since when did the phrase,
"Do you want to stay for ramyeon?"

607
00:42:59,094 --> 00:43:02,180
come to mean, "Why don't you
eat ramyeon and work all night?"

608
00:43:02,263 --> 00:43:04,683
The meaning has changed a while ago.
You didn't know?

609
00:43:06,393 --> 00:43:07,936
Now, eat up.

610
00:43:09,688 --> 00:43:12,565
And this isn't even actually boiled.
It's cup ramyeon.

611
00:43:13,108 --> 00:43:14,776
With no kimchi or pickled radish?

612
00:43:14,859 --> 00:43:17,737
Hey, you picked out good ones
in a short amount of time.

613
00:43:18,071 --> 00:43:20,115
But this definition
is a bit too abstract.

614
00:43:20,198 --> 00:43:22,534
You should specify
the actual relevant laws here.

615
00:43:22,826 --> 00:43:25,870
It'll be more effective
to present these examples verbally.

616
00:43:25,954 --> 00:43:27,414
Can you add images
and make it more visual?

617
00:43:31,626 --> 00:43:33,712
Give me some time to eat ramyeon.

618
00:43:33,795 --> 00:43:35,463
Isn't this example too much?

619
00:43:35,547 --> 00:43:37,382
Is there anything more universal?

620
00:43:40,802 --> 00:43:43,680
- What? Which one?
- This one.

621
00:43:44,305 --> 00:43:47,308
Workplace harassment
always starts quietly.

622
00:43:47,767 --> 00:43:51,688
It begins with a good morning
and an exchange of a glance.

623
00:43:52,564 --> 00:43:54,524
Then you slowly
become excluded from the team

624
00:43:54,607 --> 00:43:56,693
or get forced to do
an unreasonable amount of overtime.

625
00:43:57,152 --> 00:43:59,029
Sometimes the perpetrator goes,
"You can handle that."

626
00:43:59,112 --> 00:44:01,072
But other times, they go,
"Why do you do things your way?"

627
00:44:01,156 --> 00:44:02,407
"Do you think work is a joke?"

628
00:44:05,035 --> 00:44:06,536
What's truly scary is this.

629
00:44:06,619 --> 00:44:08,079
As these instances continue

630
00:44:08,163 --> 00:44:10,540
the victim begins
to blame themselves.

631
00:44:10,957 --> 00:44:12,459
"Am I the weird one?"

632
00:44:12,709 --> 00:44:14,002
"Am I too sensitive?"

633
00:44:14,085 --> 00:44:15,253
"Do people hate me?"

634
00:44:15,336 --> 00:44:16,671
THE VICTIM'S PSYCHOLOGICAL CHANGES

635
00:44:16,755 --> 00:44:19,799
This kind of anxiety makes the victim
accept such absurd requests.

636
00:44:23,928 --> 00:44:25,013
Everyone.

637
00:44:25,722 --> 00:44:28,058
The absurd one
is always the perpetrator.

638
00:44:28,475 --> 00:44:30,310
Do not doubt yourself or hesitate.

639
00:44:30,393 --> 00:44:32,312
Also, do not hide but report it.

640
00:44:33,980 --> 00:44:36,232
The company is obligated
to guard and protect

641
00:44:36,316 --> 00:44:38,276
the valued human resources
of its workplace.

642
00:44:40,070 --> 00:44:41,196
Do you understand?

643
00:44:41,279 --> 00:44:42,405
- Yes.
- Yes.

644
00:44:46,993 --> 00:44:48,495
Excuse me, Mr. Noh.

645
00:44:50,330 --> 00:44:52,290
- Hello, Mr. Min.
- Hello.

646
00:44:53,416 --> 00:44:56,211
Actually, I got the chance
to go to the US as an expatriate.

647
00:44:57,629 --> 00:44:58,630
Congratulations.

648
00:44:59,506 --> 00:45:02,133
I heard the opportunity
was originally meant for you.

649
00:45:02,217 --> 00:45:03,843
I hope you didn't have to step back
because of me.

650
00:45:03,927 --> 00:45:06,096
That's not something
I can just give up to someone.

651
00:45:06,513 --> 00:45:09,057
You're going because you are
more than qualified for the job.

652
00:45:10,183 --> 00:45:11,434
Thank you.

653
00:45:11,518 --> 00:45:14,646
Also, I saw that
Mr. Yoon got disciplined.

654
00:45:15,063 --> 00:45:16,940
- Is it because of me?
- Oh, no.

655
00:45:17,398 --> 00:45:19,109
We confirmed an instance of him

656
00:45:19,192 --> 00:45:21,861
leaving his workplace
during a business trip to go diving.

657
00:45:22,237 --> 00:45:24,906
That's why he got disciplined.
So don't worry about it.

658
00:45:24,989 --> 00:45:26,699
I see. Is that right?

659
00:45:28,034 --> 00:45:29,410
Have fun while you work abroad.

660
00:45:29,494 --> 00:45:31,538
I hope you go there
and get revitalized.

661
00:45:31,621 --> 00:45:32,664
I will.

662
00:45:33,206 --> 00:45:34,666
My wife is thrilled.

663
00:45:36,000 --> 00:45:37,210
I'll have a good time.

664
00:45:39,379 --> 00:45:40,421
Also

665
00:45:41,131 --> 00:45:42,257
you two look great together.

666
00:45:43,174 --> 00:45:44,968
- Sorry?
- Well...

667
00:45:56,563 --> 00:45:58,648
You can notice lots of things
when you're underwater.

668
00:46:00,150 --> 00:46:01,484
Even as you were diving with me

669
00:46:01,568 --> 00:46:03,153
your attention and mind

670
00:46:03,403 --> 00:46:05,196
were all on Ms. Joo over there.

671
00:46:06,197 --> 00:46:08,700
You kept my secret

672
00:46:09,200 --> 00:46:10,743
so I will keep yours, too.

673
00:46:11,327 --> 00:46:12,495
Don't worry.

674
00:46:12,829 --> 00:46:14,330
- Thank you.
- Sure.

675
00:46:18,918 --> 00:46:20,378
Nice shot!

676
00:46:22,005 --> 00:46:24,299
- You're ready to go out and play.
- Thank you, sir.

677
00:46:24,465 --> 00:46:27,510
I think I can play even better,
thanks to your lessons.

678
00:46:28,303 --> 00:46:29,637
Yes, right.

679
00:46:29,721 --> 00:46:31,723
I looked up the case
on Haemu Pharmaceutical

680
00:46:31,806 --> 00:46:33,433
and I did not get anything
during the handover.

681
00:46:33,725 --> 00:46:37,562
Really? Despite all those many audits

682
00:46:38,229 --> 00:46:39,647
there are no documents left behind?

683
00:46:40,064 --> 00:46:42,525
Yes. By any chance,
are you more concerned

684
00:46:42,734 --> 00:46:46,196
because Vice President Jeon Jae-yeol
was the previous president there?

685
00:46:48,239 --> 00:46:49,407
I don't know.

686
00:46:53,369 --> 00:46:55,330
Nice shot!
It's going straight to the pin!

687
00:46:55,747 --> 00:46:57,874
You got it right next to the hole.

688
00:46:58,374 --> 00:46:59,417
Gosh.

689
00:46:59,500 --> 00:47:01,252
Man, I already said
I came to play golf.

690
00:47:03,963 --> 00:47:05,089
Hey, what's up?

691
00:47:07,842 --> 00:47:08,968
Really?

692
00:47:09,636 --> 00:47:11,262
My sister-in-law is back?

693
00:47:41,042 --> 00:47:42,627
Is it because it's been a while?

694
00:47:43,211 --> 00:47:44,879
You look kind of pretty
when you sleep.

695
00:47:45,672 --> 00:47:47,006
I heard you got sick.

696
00:47:47,674 --> 00:47:49,342
Acute alcohol intoxication?

697
00:47:50,218 --> 00:47:52,470
Didn't you tell me
to get my addiction treated?

698
00:47:52,553 --> 00:47:54,931
This is freaking hilarious.

699
00:47:57,100 --> 00:47:58,142
When did you return?

700
00:47:58,226 --> 00:48:00,019
Dad gave me a hard time

701
00:48:00,103 --> 00:48:02,689
about being abroad
while you were in this mess.

702
00:48:03,982 --> 00:48:05,233
Anyway, what happened?

703
00:48:07,277 --> 00:48:09,779
I'm sure it wasn't because
you missed me so much.

704
00:48:11,656 --> 00:48:13,074
Were you that pissed

705
00:48:13,157 --> 00:48:14,951
about your brother becoming
co-vice president?

706
00:48:15,451 --> 00:48:16,953
Are you serious?

707
00:48:20,832 --> 00:48:23,126
What is this? You're boring.

708
00:48:23,543 --> 00:48:24,544
Hyun-young.

709
00:48:26,254 --> 00:48:27,297
Yes?

710
00:48:28,298 --> 00:48:29,424
Let's call it quits.

711
00:48:29,799 --> 00:48:30,800
What?

712
00:48:36,264 --> 00:48:37,348
Let's get divorced.

713
00:48:37,890 --> 00:48:39,392
What is this nonsense?

714
00:48:40,351 --> 00:48:41,936
Why should we get divorced?

715
00:48:42,020 --> 00:48:43,521
You're unhappy with me too.

716
00:48:45,690 --> 00:48:47,108
It's time to free each other.

717
00:48:49,485 --> 00:48:50,903
Let me know when you've decided.

718
00:48:52,405 --> 00:48:54,449
We can discuss the rest
through our lawyers.

719
00:48:59,287 --> 00:49:01,581
Hey, you have to tell me the reason.

720
00:49:01,956 --> 00:49:04,625
You and I didn't get married
to be happy, anyway.

721
00:49:05,376 --> 00:49:07,086
Why are you suddenly doing this?

722
00:49:07,337 --> 00:49:09,088
Have you finally lost it
just like your mom?

723
00:49:12,091 --> 00:49:13,968
I no longer want to live like this.

724
00:49:16,554 --> 00:49:17,638
You know you have

725
00:49:19,849 --> 00:49:22,393
zero chance at becoming the successor
if you divorce me, right?

726
00:49:25,146 --> 00:49:26,272
Hyun-young.

727
00:49:28,274 --> 00:49:29,901
I'll manage my own life.

728
00:49:30,985 --> 00:49:32,278
So please

729
00:49:33,446 --> 00:49:34,822
just divorce me.

730
00:49:51,506 --> 00:49:54,133
Hey, my husband is acting weird.

731
00:49:56,302 --> 00:49:57,595
Can you do some digging?

732
00:50:05,436 --> 00:50:08,064
When do you get off work?
Come to my place for dinner.

733
00:50:08,147 --> 00:50:09,190
JOO IN-A

734
00:50:09,273 --> 00:50:11,609
Why? Are you telling me
to stop by for ramyeon again?

735
00:50:18,533 --> 00:50:20,618
Today is the real deal.

736
00:50:26,916 --> 00:50:29,168
Great work today, everyone.

737
00:50:29,585 --> 00:50:30,878
- Great work today.
- Great work today.

738
00:50:34,090 --> 00:50:35,341
What was that?

739
00:50:35,425 --> 00:50:36,843
I think Ms. Joo just winked at me.

740
00:50:36,926 --> 00:50:39,053
- What?
- You must've seen something weird.

741
00:50:39,137 --> 00:50:41,931
Or she must've squinted
because she had something in her eye.

742
00:50:42,014 --> 00:50:43,933
No, I'm serious.

743
00:50:46,018 --> 00:50:47,937
- She did this.
- Do you think

744
00:50:48,438 --> 00:50:49,981
this is a sign of some sort?

745
00:50:50,064 --> 00:50:52,942
For what? Like, "You are sealed
for overtime tomorrow"?

746
00:50:53,025 --> 00:50:54,902
Her eyes must've stung.

747
00:50:54,986 --> 00:50:57,029
Stop talking nonsense. All right.

748
00:50:57,530 --> 00:50:59,490
We never got a chance to have

749
00:50:59,574 --> 00:51:01,492
a proper team dinner
after Mr. Noh got discharged.

750
00:51:01,951 --> 00:51:04,162
Why don't we go out
and eat something delicious?

751
00:51:04,245 --> 00:51:05,663
- Okay.
- I'd love to.

752
00:51:05,746 --> 00:51:07,415
Ms. Yoon?

753
00:51:07,498 --> 00:51:09,750
Well, it depends on what we eat.

754
00:51:09,834 --> 00:51:12,170
Oh, my.
I can't believe she's saying that.

755
00:51:13,588 --> 00:51:15,882
We need to eat
something really good today, then.

756
00:51:16,215 --> 00:51:18,718
It's been a while, so I'll let us use
the corporate card!

757
00:51:19,093 --> 00:51:21,095
- All right!
- Are we unleashing the company card?

758
00:51:21,179 --> 00:51:22,472
That means we have to go.

759
00:51:22,555 --> 00:51:23,723
- Let's go.
- Wait.

760
00:51:26,100 --> 00:51:27,602
I'm so sorry, but today...

761
00:51:29,479 --> 00:51:32,106
I really want to go, too.

762
00:51:35,026 --> 00:51:36,861
But I have an important appointment.

763
00:51:38,946 --> 00:51:40,281
I see.

764
00:51:41,866 --> 00:51:43,826
It's okay. We can work overtime.

765
00:51:43,910 --> 00:51:45,411
- Yes.
- Me too.

766
00:51:48,122 --> 00:51:50,333
- Overtime it is, then.
- It is.

767
00:51:57,298 --> 00:51:58,716
Let's see.

768
00:52:07,350 --> 00:52:10,394
Oh, my. What brings you
to the 14th floor, Ms. Park?

769
00:52:11,145 --> 00:52:13,064
I had to deliver something
to the Planning Team.

770
00:52:13,147 --> 00:52:14,524
Is that so?

771
00:52:29,580 --> 00:52:31,207
You must be enjoying yourself...

772
00:52:35,253 --> 00:52:36,546
caught between two men.

773
00:52:41,425 --> 00:52:42,760
Among the two men

774
00:52:43,094 --> 00:52:45,012
exactly which one
are you furious about?

775
00:52:45,263 --> 00:52:48,307
If I tell you,
will you let me have one of them?

776
00:52:49,433 --> 00:52:52,311
In that case,
it doesn't have to be Ki-jun.

777
00:52:52,979 --> 00:52:55,189
There's no need to do that.

778
00:52:56,566 --> 00:52:57,733
You two will be over shortly.

779
00:52:58,526 --> 00:53:00,778
That's how he handles
all his romantic relationships.

780
00:53:01,571 --> 00:53:02,572
Very casual.

781
00:53:07,118 --> 00:53:08,119
Let's say

782
00:53:09,453 --> 00:53:11,247
I back down from Jeon Jae-yeol.

783
00:53:12,123 --> 00:53:13,749
Can you even have him, A-jeong?

784
00:53:15,710 --> 00:53:17,587
I get that you're upset because of me

785
00:53:18,087 --> 00:53:19,380
but try not to cross the line.

786
00:53:19,839 --> 00:53:21,549
I may look quite young

787
00:53:21,632 --> 00:53:23,384
but I am an executive member
of this company.

788
00:53:23,926 --> 00:53:25,219
Executive Assistant Park A-jeong.

789
00:53:32,101 --> 00:53:33,102
Excuse me.

790
00:53:39,609 --> 00:53:42,778
- The White Blood Cell show!
- The White Blood Cell show!

791
00:53:48,326 --> 00:53:49,327
Go.

792
00:53:49,785 --> 00:53:51,245
Hey, how do you do that?

793
00:53:51,329 --> 00:53:52,997
Open up your throat

794
00:53:53,289 --> 00:53:54,540
and throw it in.

795
00:53:54,624 --> 00:53:56,709
Give me just a little bit of time.

796
00:53:57,043 --> 00:53:58,794
I'll be there soon
after I humor them.

797
00:53:58,878 --> 00:54:00,421
That's so amazing.

798
00:54:00,630 --> 00:54:04,425
- I mean, how do you do this?
- It's not a big deal.

799
00:54:05,051 --> 00:54:08,054
- You could even do an eating show.
- He could.

800
00:54:08,137 --> 00:54:10,473
Why won't the meat get cooked?
Is the heat too weak?

801
00:54:10,556 --> 00:54:12,058
No, it's the highest.

802
00:54:12,141 --> 00:54:14,602
It's taking a while
because the cut is so thick.

803
00:54:15,269 --> 00:54:17,021
Give me that. I'll do it.

804
00:54:17,104 --> 00:54:19,482
- No, I'll do it.
- It's okay. I'm on a diet, anyway.

805
00:54:19,565 --> 00:54:20,941
- I'll do it.
- No, I...

806
00:54:21,025 --> 00:54:22,360
- Give me that too.
- Goodness.

807
00:54:23,486 --> 00:54:25,988
All right! Eat your meat! Hurry!

808
00:54:26,072 --> 00:54:27,657
- All right!
- I'd love to!

809
00:54:27,740 --> 00:54:29,158
Eat up your meat!

810
00:54:29,241 --> 00:54:30,701
- I will.
- All right.

811
00:54:39,669 --> 00:54:40,753
Thanks.

812
00:54:43,130 --> 00:54:45,091
Do you not need
a toothbrush and a razor?

813
00:54:45,800 --> 00:54:48,094
- What?
- Aren't you having a hot night?

814
00:54:48,552 --> 00:54:49,762
You have to grab a toothbrush

815
00:54:49,970 --> 00:54:50,971
for your partner.

816
00:54:53,140 --> 00:54:54,975
It's been so long for me.

817
00:54:55,768 --> 00:54:57,019
Where can I find one?

818
00:54:57,436 --> 00:54:59,021
Can you drink more?

819
00:54:59,105 --> 00:55:01,857
- Yes.
- I get drunk really easily.

820
00:55:02,650 --> 00:55:04,902
- But...
- All right, everyone. Your glasses.

821
00:55:04,985 --> 00:55:06,696
Let's make a toast! Cheers!

822
00:55:06,779 --> 00:55:08,906
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

823
00:55:08,989 --> 00:55:11,534
- Drink up.
- You can take your alcohol.

824
00:55:11,617 --> 00:55:13,411
- Why don't you have another drink?
- Shall we?

825
00:55:14,912 --> 00:55:16,706
Okay. We're partying
until we drop and die tonight.

826
00:55:16,789 --> 00:55:17,915
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

827
00:55:19,208 --> 00:55:20,876
- Chug your drink!
- Yes!

828
00:55:22,837 --> 00:55:25,256
- Okay.
- Who needs a drink?

829
00:55:26,132 --> 00:55:27,967
Now, another toast!

830
00:55:29,009 --> 00:55:30,469
- Cheers.
- It's the last one.

831
00:55:30,553 --> 00:55:32,096
- The last one.
- The last one!

832
00:55:32,179 --> 00:55:35,349
- It's the last drink here!
- Hey!

833
00:55:35,433 --> 00:55:36,892
That was so good.

834
00:55:37,435 --> 00:55:38,978
Where are we going for round two?

835
00:55:39,061 --> 00:55:41,188
- A karaoke room.
- Let's go karaokeing.

836
00:55:42,565 --> 00:55:44,108
- Mr. Noh. Where's Mr. Noh?
- Yes!

837
00:55:47,361 --> 00:55:48,446
- Hey!
- Come back.

838
00:55:48,821 --> 00:55:50,781
- You can't run away.
- Get back here.

839
00:55:50,865 --> 00:55:52,199
You can't leave today.

840
00:55:52,283 --> 00:55:55,411
- Not today.
- You're the hero tonight.

841
00:55:55,494 --> 00:55:58,748
Drunk as a fish

842
00:55:58,831 --> 00:56:02,334
I am dead drunk

843
00:56:02,793 --> 00:56:06,088
I have fallen

844
00:56:06,172 --> 00:56:09,216
For the scent of your love

845
00:56:09,383 --> 00:56:10,760
I have fallen!

846
00:56:11,093 --> 00:56:14,346
Oh, oh, oh

847
00:56:14,430 --> 00:56:16,348
- All right!
- Sing it!

848
00:57:07,691 --> 00:57:08,692
My goodness.

849
00:57:16,450 --> 00:57:17,952
- Hello?
- Okay!

850
00:57:18,994 --> 00:57:19,995
I'm sorry.

851
00:57:20,246 --> 00:57:23,165
They're holding me back
like today is my last day on earth.

852
00:57:23,791 --> 00:57:25,376
I'm so sorry.

853
00:57:26,335 --> 00:57:28,671
I think it'll take
just a little longer.

854
00:57:28,754 --> 00:57:29,964
Is that so?

855
00:57:30,422 --> 00:57:31,799
Well, I can't help it.

856
00:57:32,091 --> 00:57:34,552
Team dinners are a part of work,
so make sure you stay until the end.

857
00:57:38,806 --> 00:57:40,474
At least he won't be hungry.

858
00:57:41,767 --> 00:57:44,061
That means I'll have to eat

859
00:57:44,144 --> 00:57:46,730
which means my tummy will stick out.

860
00:57:46,814 --> 00:57:48,065
But what can I do?

861
00:57:54,405 --> 00:57:55,406
What?

862
00:57:58,075 --> 00:57:59,285
He said he'd be late.

863
00:58:00,452 --> 00:58:02,204
What is this? A surprise?

864
00:58:04,206 --> 00:58:05,457
You're here already?

865
00:58:13,173 --> 00:58:15,175
- Hey! I'm feeling too great!
- No.

866
00:58:15,259 --> 00:58:16,927
- Just one more bottle.
- Oh, no.

867
00:58:17,011 --> 00:58:19,013
Drunk as a fish

868
00:58:19,096 --> 00:58:20,097
Goodbye!

869
00:58:20,180 --> 00:58:21,515
- Goodbye!
- Boys!

870
00:58:21,724 --> 00:58:23,225
- I'm feeling too great.
- Bye, now.

871
00:58:23,309 --> 00:58:24,894
Time to go!

872
00:58:24,977 --> 00:58:26,896
Come on, man. One more bottle.

873
00:58:28,022 --> 00:58:29,940
- Now.
- All right. I get it.

874
00:58:30,024 --> 00:58:31,150
Okay, then.

875
00:58:31,525 --> 00:58:33,527
Mr. Noh, let's grab
just one more drink.

876
00:58:33,611 --> 00:58:35,696
- Great. I just need one more drink.
- Awesome.

877
00:58:35,779 --> 00:58:37,072
- No.
- What?

878
00:58:37,156 --> 00:58:38,908
That's all for today.
Maybe next time, okay?

879
00:58:38,991 --> 00:58:40,492
- There is no next time.
- There's only today.

880
00:58:40,576 --> 00:58:41,660
- No.
- Where are you going?

881
00:58:41,744 --> 00:58:43,704
- Mr. Noh!
- Just one more drink!

882
00:58:43,996 --> 00:58:45,956
- Mr. Noh!
- Don't go!

883
00:58:50,544 --> 00:58:52,546
You must've been expecting someone.

884
00:58:52,630 --> 00:58:53,923
Yes, I don't know why you're here

885
00:58:54,006 --> 00:58:56,133
but I want you to keep it short
and leave.

886
00:58:58,260 --> 00:58:59,720
I may sound like an idiot

887
00:59:00,763 --> 00:59:03,057
but even as I married
someone who wasn't you

888
00:59:03,641 --> 00:59:05,768
I never once had thought
I had lost you.

889
00:59:08,228 --> 00:59:10,022
That's a selfish thought.

890
00:59:10,397 --> 00:59:12,650
You said you'd be on my side.

891
00:59:14,360 --> 00:59:16,111
I think I lived my life
depending on those words.

892
00:59:17,488 --> 00:59:18,739
You said you were
honoring your words.

893
00:59:20,366 --> 00:59:21,450
I don't care what it is.

894
00:59:24,954 --> 00:59:28,082
I'm getting a divorce.
I told my wife, too.

895
00:59:33,963 --> 00:59:35,422
What do you think you're doing?

896
00:59:36,674 --> 00:59:38,592
What kind of response
did you expect from me?

897
00:59:39,301 --> 00:59:43,305
"Wow, Jae-yeol is divorcing!
I'm going to date him now!"

898
00:59:43,514 --> 00:59:45,265
- Did you think I'd say that?
- I know

899
00:59:45,349 --> 00:59:47,309
I can't get you back
even if I get divorced.

900
00:59:48,894 --> 00:59:50,104
I know

901
00:59:50,938 --> 00:59:52,648
I've lost you for good.

902
00:59:54,566 --> 00:59:57,945
But no matter what I do,
I couldn't let my feelings go.

903
01:00:00,280 --> 01:00:02,116
The least I can do
is be honest with my feelings.

904
01:00:03,617 --> 01:00:04,952
That's why I'm divorcing.

905
01:00:06,286 --> 01:00:07,955
It's not because of you
but because of me.

906
01:00:09,540 --> 01:00:10,791
It's killing me.

907
01:00:20,009 --> 01:00:21,385
I regret everything, In-a.

908
01:00:29,309 --> 01:00:30,936
I'm sorry.
I got here too late, didn't I?

909
01:00:37,818 --> 01:00:39,278
The one
you had been waiting for is here.

910
01:00:41,447 --> 01:00:43,949
I'm done talking, so excuse me.

911
01:01:21,695 --> 01:01:23,781
Wow, you prepared a lot of things.

912
01:01:25,616 --> 01:01:27,326
Did you make the pasta yourself?

913
01:01:27,868 --> 01:01:29,661
It looks great.

914
01:01:31,330 --> 01:01:32,664
I got these delivered.

915
01:01:37,377 --> 01:01:39,338
Good call. Delivery food is the best.

916
01:01:39,588 --> 01:01:42,216
Haemu Group's Head of Audit
couldn't have had any time to cook.

917
01:01:43,300 --> 01:01:45,469
You need to use all your free time
to stare at my face.

918
01:01:46,678 --> 01:01:47,846
Aren't you going to ask?

919
01:01:50,015 --> 01:01:51,391
You're in a foul mood.

920
01:01:51,725 --> 01:01:52,851
And you must be curious.

921
01:01:53,560 --> 01:01:55,938
Stop beating around the bush
and just ask me.

922
01:02:03,904 --> 01:02:04,905
I do want to know.

923
01:02:05,739 --> 01:02:07,324
And yes, I'm in a foul mood.

924
01:02:08,659 --> 01:02:09,701
But I

925
01:02:10,369 --> 01:02:12,037
do not want to make myself ask.

926
01:02:13,330 --> 01:02:14,832
It's probably something
between you two.

927
01:02:25,134 --> 01:02:26,426
I guess today isn't a good day.

928
01:02:27,261 --> 01:02:28,720
And you prepared so much.

929
01:02:35,978 --> 01:02:38,230
Don't drink, and go to sleep early.

930
01:02:38,939 --> 01:02:40,232
You have to be at work tomorrow.

931
01:02:41,483 --> 01:02:42,484
Okay?

932
01:02:43,610 --> 01:02:44,653
I'll get going now.

933
01:03:47,549 --> 01:03:48,634
Don't go.

934
01:03:57,434 --> 01:03:58,727
Stay by my side.

935
01:06:13,153 --> 01:06:14,196
Joo In-a...

936
01:06:16,031 --> 01:06:18,575
What on earth is she to you?

937
01:06:20,160 --> 01:06:22,204
She's someone I would die with.

938
01:06:23,789 --> 01:06:25,916
Can you even give up everything
for that woman?

939
01:06:26,583 --> 01:06:27,667
If I must.

940
01:06:28,126 --> 01:06:29,836
Let's say
I back down from Jeon Jae-yeol.

941
01:06:30,837 --> 01:06:32,339
Can you even have him, A-jeong?

942
01:06:49,648 --> 01:06:51,858
My gosh. We almost ran late.

943
01:06:52,109 --> 01:06:53,735
And I'm never late to work.

944
01:06:53,819 --> 01:06:56,613
And I never wear the same tie
two days in a row.

945
01:06:57,406 --> 01:06:58,865
That's the thing about dating.

946
01:06:58,949 --> 01:07:01,451
New definitions are introduced
to your dictionary.

947
01:07:01,535 --> 01:07:02,911
You're a smooth talker.

948
01:07:03,620 --> 01:07:04,913
But I can't accept being late.

949
01:07:05,997 --> 01:07:07,582
Have another great day.

950
01:07:10,001 --> 01:07:11,711
- You too.
- Thanks.

951
01:07:19,428 --> 01:07:20,971
Good morning.

952
01:07:21,054 --> 01:07:22,681
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

953
01:07:22,764 --> 01:07:23,932
Good morning.

954
01:07:25,934 --> 01:07:27,227
SENT BY NONAME
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

955
01:07:40,574 --> 01:07:42,701
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

956
01:07:45,871 --> 01:07:47,622
- What?
- What is this?

957
01:07:47,706 --> 01:07:48,790
Did you see it?

958
01:07:51,751 --> 01:07:54,171
I'd like to report
on Ms. Joo In-a's private life.

959
01:07:55,881 --> 01:07:57,841
Ms. Joo In-a remains aloof

960
01:07:57,924 --> 01:08:00,343
while keeping an eye on others
and punishing them

961
01:08:00,969 --> 01:08:03,180
but she's actually a hypocrite

962
01:08:03,722 --> 01:08:05,348
who lives
a very complicated private life.

963
01:08:06,433 --> 01:08:07,476
I attach

964
01:08:08,268 --> 01:08:11,438
a picture of Ms. Joo In-a
with her superior, who is married.

965
01:09:11,289 --> 01:09:14,209
FILING FOR LOVE

966
01:09:42,320 --> 01:09:43,655
Is the rumor about Ms. Joo true?

967
01:09:43,738 --> 01:09:47,117
So who's the man in the photo
that you exchanged greetings with?

968
01:09:47,409 --> 01:09:49,661
I know he's the vice president,
this feels way out of...

969
01:09:49,744 --> 01:09:52,247
Don't frown. You'll get wrinkles.

970
01:09:52,330 --> 01:09:54,416
I'll be an iron fortress! Let's go!

971
01:09:54,499 --> 01:09:55,750
Are you crying?

972
01:09:55,959 --> 01:09:57,544
You know, Ms. Joo's mail...

973
01:09:57,627 --> 01:10:00,922
The sender's location was traced
to Mr. Noh Ki-jun's home.

974
01:10:01,006 --> 01:10:03,800
Are you going to save me
like a knight in shining armor?

975
01:10:03,883 --> 01:10:04,926
Just say I did it.

976
01:10:05,010 --> 01:10:07,095
Mr. Noh Ki-jun will face
disciplinary action.

977
01:10:08,054 --> 01:10:09,306
I'll take responsibility.

978
01:10:22,777 --> 01:10:24,779
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim
